### [ATTACK] Cancel — inject extra fields (should be stripped)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{activeSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Trying to inject extra fields",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false,
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "balance_due": 0,
  "agreed_by": "hacker-id"
}

###

### [ATTACK] Cancel — forged JWT
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{activeSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJub25lIn0.eyJzdWIiOiJoYWNrZXIiLCJyb2xlIjoiU1VQRVJfQURNSU4iLCJzZXNzaW9uSWQiOiJmYWtlIn0.
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Forged JWT cancel attempt",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false
}

###

### [ATTACK] Cancel — double cancel (idempotency check)
# First cancel succeeds, second should return 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{activeSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "First cancel",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false
}

###

# Run immediately after the above
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{activeSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Second cancel — should 409",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false
}

###

### [ATTACK] Cancel — HTTP verb tampering (GET on POST route)
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{activeSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### [ATTACK] Cancel — oversized JSON body
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{activeSubId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "reason": "Legitimate reason",
  "cancel_at_period_end": false,
  "junk": ""
}
